org.gstreamer

Class ElementFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gstreamer.lowlevel.NativeValue
      • org.gstreamer.lowlevel.Handle
        • org.gstreamer.lowlevel.NativeObject
          • org.gstreamer.lowlevel.RefCountedObject
            • org.gstreamer.GObject
              • org.gstreamer.GstObject
                • org.gstreamer.PluginFeature
                  • org.gstreamer.ElementFactory

  • public class ElementFactory
extends PluginFeature
    ElementFactory is used to create instances of elements. Use the find(java.lang.String) and create(java.lang.String) methods to create element instances or use make(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) as a convenient shortcut.

      • listGetElement

        public static List<ElementFactory> listGetElement(ElementFactory.ElementFactoryListType type,
                                  PluginFeature.Rank minrank)
        Get a list of factories that match the given type. Only elements with a rank greater or equal to minrank will be returned. The list of factories is returned by decreasing rank.
        Parameters:
        type - a ElementFactory.ElementFactoryListType
        minrank - Minimum rank
        Returns:
        a List of ElementFactory elements.

      • listFilter

        public static List<ElementFactory> listFilter(List<ElementFactory> list,
                              Caps caps,
                              PadDirection direction,
                              boolean subsetonly)
        Filter out all the elementfactories in list that can handle caps in the given direction. If subsetonly is true, then only the elements whose pads templates are a complete superset of caps will be returned. Else any element whose pad templates caps can intersect with caps will be returned.
        Parameters:
        list - a List of ElementFactory to filter
        caps - a Caps
        direction - a PadDirection to filter on
        subsetonly - whether to filter on caps subsets or not.
        Returns:
        a List of ElementFactory elements that match the given requisits.

      • listGetElementFilter

        public static List<ElementFactory> listGetElementFilter(ElementFactory.ElementFactoryListType type,
                                        PluginFeature.Rank minrank,
                                        Caps caps,
                                        PadDirection direction,
                                        boolean subsetonly)
        Get a list of factories that match the given parameter. It is a combination of listGetElement and listFilter passing all the results of the first call to the second. This method improves performance because there is no need to map to java list the elements returned by the first call.
        Parameters:
        type - a ElementFactory.ElementFactoryListType
        minrank - Minimum rank
        caps - a Caps
        direction - a PadDirection to filter on
        subsetonly - whether to filter on caps subsets or not.
        Returns:
        a List of ElementFactory elements that match the given requisits.
